08/12/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The war crimes chamber at Belgrade's district court sentenced a former Bosnian Serb soldier to 13 years in prison Monday (December 7th) for war crimes against civilians during the 1992-1995 conflict. Nenad Malic was found guilty of murdering two Muslims and for the attempted murder of another civilian in the town of Stari Majdan in 1992. Malic, a Serbian citizen, was arrested in January. (Beta, Tanjug, B92, RTRS - 07/12/09)
